ame Theory proposed by David Laitin. It forecasts a 3±1 language outcome for most African countries. This outcome supports the "three language formula" now called for by the United Nations Development Program (UNDP).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aJapanese languagexStudy and teachingxForeign speakers. 0aLanguage and languagesxStudy and teachingzUnited States. 0aLanguage teachersxTraining ofzUnited States. 0aSecond language acquisition. 4aSoziolinguistik. 4aSprachplanung. 4aSprachpolitik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aAfrican studies.  aAnthropological linguistics.  aEmerging literacies.  aEndangered languages.  aLanguage planning.  aLanguage policy.  aMultilingualism.  aSociolinguistics.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Linguistics and Semiotics  2000-2014 (EN)z978311023845708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton Backlist 2000-2015z978311074296108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2012z9783110288995oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LINGUISTICS AND LITERATURE 2012z978311028890208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2012z9783110288896oZDB-23-DGA0 cprintz978193407810540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978193407811240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781934078112423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781934078112/original  a978-3-11-023845-7  DGBA Backlist Linguistics and Se